Attending the 2023 Go Red For Women Luncheon was such an honor! As a firefighter, I have responded to countless emergencies and deaths caused by cardiac diseases. I learned today that 1 in 3 women will die of cardiac issues in the US. 

The #NashGoRed mission aims to change this statistic. I have seen the incredible need for their work firsthand in our communities and I cannot wait to further partner with this organization. 

This is why we are proud that every one of our hundreds of @southernsitter babysitters are #CPRcertified. 

Thank you @american_heart for having me today!

#internationalfirefightersday

This journey has challenged me in ways I couldn’t have ever imagined. In the last year and a half, I’ve held the hands of dying patients taking their last breath. I’ve hugged parents who have just lost their child. I’ve held it together during a call just to fall apart in the car after losing a patient that we tried everything to save. I’ve seen the tragic effects of heart diseases, drug overdoses, and car accidents take the lives of my own community members. 

But I have also witnessed families come together in their worst moments. I have seen people support their neighbors through tragedy and loss. I’ve learned to appreciate the precious gift of life in a way I could never have imagined. I’ve raised $15,000+ for MCFD, served as a Public Information Officer, and shared fire safety with countless students. 

The hardest moments are worth it for the little girls that look at me and ask “I can be a firefighter too?” Yes. And you can be amazing at it. 

I am so thankful to have started this journey and absolutely love love love this work. Thank you to all of our first responders today. ❤️

Isaiah 6:8

Then I heard the voice of the Lord saying, “Whom shall I send? And who will go for us?” And I said, “Here am I. Send me.”

SWIFTWATER OPERATIONS CERTIFIED with the BEST team! Had such a blast spending these last 3 days on the Ocoee and Hiwassee rivers! We learned how to defensively swim through high speed currents, flip boats that have been overturned, rig rope rescue systems, throw rescue bags, and we paddled until we dropped 😂

This FEMA training certifies firefighters to respond to flooding emergencies and swiftwater involved rescues. So thankful for the memories made with my volunteer department on this challenging and fun weekend!

Biggest smiles as I head into the most amazing week! On Saturday, I am honored and humbled to spend the day with Gold Star Families on Fort Campbell at the annual Gold Star family picnic. I am so thankful to have this opportunity to hear their stories and bring light to a day of honor and remembrance. I can’t wait for this day!

It hit me last night how special it I get to be apart of this event before stepping into competition week at @misstennesseecompetition. To compete with my heart full of the families who have given everything is beyond words. It is my deepest honor to perform at this event just before leaving for a week where I get to share the stories of military personnel who have changed my life. 

Thankful thankful thankful 💙

So so thankful for this special first day! I was honored to receive the overall Servant Leader Community Service award, 4th Runner Up Public Relations Award for over $6,000 in ad pages sold, AND current 3rd place recognition for the HundredX Survey Collection Fundraiser for raising $1,800+!

Can’t wait for the rest of this amazing week! Wow!!

I’ve had some time to reflect on this life changing week and I am left with so much joy and gratitude. There are truly no words to describe this incredible experience, but I going to try my best!

Oh. My. Goodness. I received the Overall Interview Award, Overall Community Service Award, and I was named First Alternate to our gorgeous Miss Tennessee @brandeealexis. 
I made incredible friendships that already feel lifelong. I received thousands in scholarships as the Top 3 Ad Page Sales Winner and Top 2 HundredX Fundraiser Winner. Through these initiatives, I was able to raise over $8,000 for women’s scholarships. 

Brandee, it was such an honor to hold your hands as you first stepped into this incredible year. I can’t wait to see all you do for our state this year. ❤️ 

To my friends, family, and businesses that supported me throughout this competition: I can’t thank you enough. I felt your support and prayers every day. 

Robertson County, it was an such an honor to represent you! I can’t wait to continue to serve in this role. Thankful thankful thankful

Savannah Maddison, NR-EMT 💚 

It was such an honor to attend the top Emergency Medicine Program in the country! I LOVED my class and was honored to graduate Summa Cum Laude with a 4.0 GPA and a FIRST TRY pass on the National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians Exam! 🙌🏻

So thankful for the @missamericatn scholarships that allowed me to attend this prestigious program! As First Runner Up in June, I was able to apply over $3,000 in scholarships towards this opportunity. 

I am also so thankful to all of the incredible instructors and preceptors that helped me to succeed. So excited to utilize this licensure to better serve my community!

My favorite event at @missamerica this week! As a 2024 Women of Impact for the @american_heart association, this event was so special to me. 

Through my work as a volunteer firefighter and EMT, I have seen countless deaths that may have been prevented by the administration of CPR by bystanders. 

My partnership with AHA has already certified thousands of women and taught countless more hands-only CPR. I am so proud to serve as the Chair of the @goredforwomen AHA TN Pulse Board and continue this mission!🚨

This is why we ensure that every @southernsitter is CPR certified and SIDS aware. This is why we educate our communities on hands-only CPR. This is why we host events for young women to learn about careers in STEM. Join me in the #GOREDFORWOMEN movement.❤️
